OLTP: Online Transaction Processing is an operational data which consists of the orginal source of the data. It helps in controlling and 
running basic business tasks. The data in short reveals about the ongoing business processes. The processing speed is very fast compared 
to OLAP. It has rigorous backups. It deals with simple queries. 


OLAP: Online Analytical Processing is a consolidated data which consists of the data taken from various OLTP Databases. It helps with 
planning, problem solving and decision support. The data has multi-dimensional views of different business activities. The processing speed depends on 
data involved and might take hours for complex queries to execute. Instead of backup, it reloads the OLTP data as a recovery method. OLAP
delas with complex queries which involves aggregations. 
